@page "/"

<PageTitle>AeroResponse</PageTitle>

<section class="hero-section">
    <div class="hero-overlay">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <span class="eyebrow">Aircraft Emergency Response Training Simulator</span>
            <h1>Train for critical in-flight emergencies.</h1>
            <p>
                AeroResponse is a web-based aviation training platform that allows pilots and trainees
                to practise emergency response through interactive cockpit simulations, aircraft scenarios,
                performance tracking, and membership-based access.
            </p>

            <div class="hero-actions">
                <a href="/membership" class="btn-primary">Start Training</a>
                <a href="/scenarios" class="btn-secondary">View Scenarios</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="feature-section">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <h2>Built for realistic emergency response training</h2>
        <p>Interactive, aviation-focused, and designed around decision-making under pressure.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-grid">
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">✈️</div>
            <h3>Aircraft Selection</h3>
            <p>Select aircraft such as Boeing 737, Airbus A320, Boeing 787, and Gulfstream.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">🚨</div>
            <h3>Emergency Scenarios</h3>
            <p>Train on engine fire, depressurisation, hydraulic failure, bird strike, and more.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">🎛️</div>
            <h3>Interactive Cockpit</h3>
            <p>Use throttle controls, fuel switches, fire handles, checklists, and alerts.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">📊</div>
            <h3>Performance Analytics</h3>
            <p>Track reaction time, procedure accuracy, decision-making, and training history.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>